$ bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --zookeeper localhost:2181   --topic topic2 --from-beginning

```
Then on another machine I start experimenting with node.js and kafka-node.

Firstly a producer that puts a few hundred thousand messages into the topics. Then a consumer to get them back again. Which both worked.

The code which triggered the server blow up was only a little test of getting latest offsets:

```
// Fetch first or last offsets or from a given time.
