2222,IssuesEvent,2015-12-05 17:51:46+00:00,47325685,agronholm/apscheduler,130003,agronholm,,,opened,Using CronTrigger with any fields with 0 will be ignored ,[],[],0,"scheduler.add_cron_job(cron_func, hour = 18, minute = 20, second = 0)

should only call cron_func at 6:20 pm once, but because the 0 is ignored it is called multiple times.

Not sure if there's a more elegant way, but attached is a patch that should fix the issue.

----------------------------------------
- Bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/agronholm/apscheduler/issue/9
- Originally reported by: [syu](http://bitbucket.org/syu)
- Originally created at: 2011-03-13T03:35:14.137
",{},{}
2223,IssuesEvent,2018-03-07 21:55:46+00:00,54828252,agronholm/apscheduler,9842735,csanz91,,,opened,Cron jobs executes more times than desired when using jitter,[],[],0,"When using the jitter option in a scheduled cron jobs, for example using the code from the documentation:
 
`# Run the `job_function` every sharp hour with an extra-delay picked randomly in a [-120,+120] seconds window.
sched.add_job(job_function, 'cron', hour='*', jitter=120)`

if the job is scheduled before the sharp hour then the job will be scheduled for the same hour again. For example:

- A Job is defined to be runned at sharp hours.

- Job is scheduled to run at 14:59:51

- Job runs at 14:59:51 but its scheduled to run at 15:00:02 again.
In this case we only want the job to run once at ~15:00:00.

Attached is a small piece of code to test this behaiviour: [test.zip](https://github.com/agronholm/apscheduler/files/1791019/test.zip)

",{},{}
