3162,IssuesEvent,2017-10-08 20:12:54+00:00,85780522,fgmacedo/python-statemachine,281007,fgmacedo,,,closed,Transition `on_execute` should accept the destination state as result even if there's only one destination.,"[{'id': 566325964, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/fgmacedo/python-statemachine/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]",[],0,"* Python State Machine version: 0.5.0
* Python version: Any.
* Operating System: Any.

### Description

If you define a state machine with a transition that has an `on_execute` callback, you can't return the desired state if there's only one option. The syntax `return <result, desired state>` only works if multiple destination states are defined.
",{},{}
