4785,IssuesEvent,2016-01-08 18:07:12+00:00,8435559,zopefoundation/Products.ZCatalog,483109,hannosch,1163184,zopefoundation,closed,Make query planner configurable,[],[],12,"Here at der Freitag (http://www.freitag.de) we faced a huge performance problem: the query planner, to create the plan was trying to load all objects on the indexes, this should not be a problem if the database is not so big, but in our case we have **~3 million** objects on the main database and **~7 million objects** on the portal_catalog mount point.

We tried to use the master branch with Hanno's https://github.com/zopefoundation/Products.ZCatalog/commit/3b2f2f1b42e5a51c71c337e052f76586e501776e patch but that was still making our instances to take an awful amount of time to start.

In the end @ctheune wrote a quick patch to completely disable the query planner: https://github.com/ctheune/Products.ZCatalog/commit/fd4db1c9fa5b4bc37e6b95ca5df02596412bff3a

He tried to apply it on top of current master but without luck, still that commit is a quick hack, that's why I'm opening this issue, to ask if it would make sense to make the query planner configurable so that users can opt-out of it.

We are using Plone 4.2.6 with Products.ZCatalog 2.13.26
I would be glad to help on providing more information if needed.",{},{}
