5372,IssuesEvent,2017-08-25 18:13:04+00:00,6624198,bloomreach/s4cmd,15657567,olenm,2058330,bloomreach,opened,"pip3 install works, running fails as s4cmd defaults to python2",[],[],0,"on mac sierra 10.12.4

- install via `pip3 install s4cmd` (default fails due to https://github.com/bloomreach/s4cmd/issues/73, works after the fix by ajkerrigan-mdsol)
- run via cli `s4cmd`  fails due to python2 being the default on the system (and s4cmd is a bash script wrapper for python)


I would suggest the install auto-detect which version of python to use on install and use this in the s4cmd bash-wrapper.

Thanks

",{},{}
