5769,IssuesEvent,2017-02-22 19:25:23+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,6178947,JasonQSong,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Find a good way to preserve the flexibility of Node.js native REPL,[],[],0,"Reference: contrib/node/src/python/pants/contrib/node/tasks/node_repl.py:L73

REPL task is hard to take over Node.js native REPL for the following reasons:
1. Node.js can simply start from the package source root because node package is self-contained.
2. There's no simple entry point (binary) for Node.js packages. A package may start from node, babel-node, babel-polyfill, webpack, etc.
In addition, since the repl task is modifing the package.json and there is no lockdown, it is impossible to use yarnpkg to start REPL unless the dependency resolver is removed.",{},{}
5785,IssuesEvent,2016-09-29 18:58:45+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1743873,mateor,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,"safe_mkdir will not clean symlinks, like the current_results_dir.",[],[],0,"Since the `current` directory is a symlink the delete does not go through. This is what is passed by simple_codgen_task, for instance.

          if not vt.valid:
            safe_mkdir(results_dir, clean=True)

I believe this is live in node_resolve, but if not it is still a bug waiting to hit on task subclasses. I think that the proper answer is for safe_mkdir to clean the realpath.

Then there is the followup question of should safe_mkdir check to make sure that the passed directory is under the buildroot?",{},{}
