5986,IssuesEvent,2017-11-08 23:42:35+00:00,30888372,nccgroup/opinel,7882431,gforinger,4067082,nccgroup,opened,Use MFA auth when mfa-code is provided,[],[],0,"Currently, If you specify an mfa-code on the Scout2 command line, it will be ignored without any warnings or errors.

In Scout2, __main.py__ calls read_creds from opinel/utils/credentials.py

In opinel/utils/credentials.py, the read creds function only does an init_sts_session with the mfa-code if the force_init bool is set to True, but that never happens if your ~/.aws/credentials file doesn't contain a SessionToken already. If the session token doesn't exist, it should probably set force_init to True.",{},{}
