6231,IssuesEvent,2017-10-15 15:25:48+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,3291951,matt-gardner,5667695,allenai,opened,Update website to report training variance,[],[],0,"We will keep getting people confused about why their training run doesn't match our models' numbers until we have some discussion of this on the website where we report performance numbers.  Even though anyone who's trained a neural net knows how finicky they are, they often don't make the connection that the finickiness is often due just to training variance, and that a reference implementation of someone else's model will _also_ be finicky.  [Here's](https://github.com/allenai/allennlp/issues/379#issuecomment-336718417) some text that should be a good starting place for something to put on the website.",{},{}
