6326,IssuesEvent,2015-05-04 21:44:45+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,1360539,bacongobbler,6117407,deis,closed,App availability problems when stopping a node,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/scheduler', 'name': 'scheduler', 'color': 'fad8c7'}]",[],13,"If an app has all of its instances running on the same node, and that node shuts down, the app will be unavailable, initially producing gateway timeout errors, then displaying the generic ""Welcome to nginx"" page.

Two improvements could remedy this:

1. Allow a node to be seamlessly removed from the cluster (bring up new services/apps on other nodes, route new requests to other nodes, allow pending requests to finish, shut down old services/apps).  Is this already possible somehow?
2. Ensure apps scaled to more than one instance are placed on different nodes, making them more robust against single node failures.

Deis is usually quick to recover from the above, but it seems to become a significant availability problem when the node in question also holds the builder service and the builder service moves to a node which does not have the builder image (as happens nearly every time in EC2 with auto load-balancing).  In that case, it seems to require multiple minutes for the app to recover.",{},{}
6336,IssuesEvent,2015-03-07 15:01:51+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,193115,haf,6117407,deis,opened,Can I extract time-series data easily from the platform?,[],[],0,"I'm trying to get up to speed on the deis platform, and was wondering if there are easy APIs that I can point in the direction of a ""resource""/service -- Heka in this case -- which can then ship to another resource -- InfluxDB for saving and monitoring of time-series data? I'm at this point looking for docs on how to instrument the deployed containers, or even better, use their internal metrics, so that I can react to adverse conditions when it's deployed.

I haven't been able to find that much docs on this; are there any around?",{},{}
6337,IssuesEvent,2016-04-04 15:49:46+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,1360539,bacongobbler,6117407,deis,closed,[meta] Deis v2 Beta,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/v2', 'name': 'v2', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}]",[],15,"Meta issue for Deis v2 Beta; as specific issues are filed in other repos, we will link them back to this issue.

[Beta Issues Search](https://github.com/issues?q=is%3Aopen+user%3Adeis+user%3Ahelm+milestone%3Av2.0-beta1+sort%3Aupdated-desc)

## Beta Goals

The Beta period is focused on stabilizing backing services, reaching availability and recoverability targets. Technology choices for each of backing services should be well understood for each of our blessed configurations.

e2e testing infrastructure for v2 platform should be in place. The long-running/soak tests are a requirement to leave beta (see test target below).

Beta should also exit with a strong opinion about production and staging configurations and how best to go from zero to kubernetes.

## Project-level

* [x] Documentation: deis/deis#4889
    * ~~Services that support TLS should be deployed with TLS by default~~
* [x] **Availability target:**
    * Components should be recoverable with manual intervention and documentation
    * Self-healing components where possible
* [ ] **Recoverability target:**
    * Given a backup of the platform, restoring to a known-good k8s cluster should take < 1 hour
* [x] **Infrastructure targets:**
    * Documentation for standup on AWS via [coreos-kubernetes](https://github.com/coreos/coreos-kubernetes)
    * Documentation for standup on GKE
* [x] **Installation target:**
    * Automated via Helm
* [ ] **Test target:**
    * [x] workflow-e2e fully automated
    * [ ] workflow-e2e green
* [x] **Debugging target:**
    * [x] Deis Workflow Manager

## Meta
* [x] all project components adhere to `deis/prototype-repo`
* ~~all components output version information on startup~~
* [x] all components logs available through logging sub-system
* [x] all kubernetes requirements documented (DeamonSets, Versions, etc): deis/deis#4889
* [x] components audited for standard storage layout: deis/deis#4852
* [x] components audited for port usage: deis/deis#4853

## Release Checklist
* [x] update documentation from alpha to beta
* [x] update workflow charts

## Components

### Client
* [x] Client v2 master builds pushed to bintray

### Controller [deis/workflow](https://github.com/deis/workflow)
* [x] Django upgrade
* [x] Remove etcd depdendency: deis/workflow#96
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to platform monitor component~~
* Availability
    * [x] Strategy: RC=1
    * [x] Needs health check that hits database: deis/workflow#305
    * [x] Remove etcd interactions: deis/workflow#96

### Database [deis/postgres](https://github.com/deis/postgres)
* [x] Availability
    * [x] Strategy: RC=1
    * [x] Needs health check: deis/postgres#30
    * [x] Wal-e shipping: deis/postgres#31
    * [x] Wal-e backups shipping: deis/postgres#32
    * [ ] Logical backup shipping: deis/postgres#33
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to platform monitor component~~
* [x] Recoverability: documented disaster recovery through backups + restore: deis/postgres#34
* [x] Testing: single node failure, recovery

### ~~Etcd [deis/etcd](https://github.com/deis/etcd)~~
* ~~Availability: HA configuration deployed by default~~
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to platform monitor component~~
* ~~Recoverability: documented backup + restore~~
* ~~Testing: single, multi-node failure, recovery~~

### Registry [deis/registry](https://github.com/deis/registry)
* [x] Availability:
    * [x] Strategy: RC=1
    * [x] Add health check: deis/registry#19
    * [x] Use cluster-configured object storage: deis/registry#20
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to monitor component~~
* [ ] Recoverability: documented backup + restore
* [x] Security: Document that insecure registry must be enabled on kubernetes cluster

### Object storage
* [ ] Off-cluster storage
    * Setup and configuration documented to consume object storage via: (https://github.com/deis/workflow/issues/360)
        * [ ] AWS S3
        * [ ] GCS (in compatability mode)
        * [ ] Ceph Object Storage
    * [ ] `helm generate` works for all of the above scenarios (https://github.com/deis/charts/issues/95)
    * [x] audit and normalize environment variables for all consumers of object storage (ACCESS_KEY, etc.)
        * builder, registry, slugrunner, slugbuilder, postgres/database
* [x] minio [deis/minio](https://github.com/deis/minio)
    * Availability:
        * [x] Strategy: RC=1
        * [x] Add health check: deis/minio#54
    *  ~~SSL/TLS by default~~
    *  Persistent Storage (K8S Volumes/Background Sync)
* ~~RiakCS~~
    * ~~Tested persistent volumes~~

### Router [deis/router](https://github.com/deis/router)
* [x] Router configuration and sub-system documented
* [x] basic http routing to services
* [x] Terminate SSL for workflow/controller
* [x] Terminate SSL for customer applications
* [ ] Metrics: expose operational metrics to monitor component
* Availability
     * Strategy: RC=1 out of box (gives us ssl session resumption)

### Builder [deis/builder](https://github.com/deis/builder)
* [x] `Dockerfile` functionality
* [x] Buildpack functionality
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to monitor component~~
* Availability
    * [x] Strategy: RC=1
    * [x] Needs: health check, should check k8s api service: deis/builder#92
    * [x] Fix user key acquisition: deis/builder#81 deis/builder#122
    * [x] Fix app deletion: https://github.com/deis/builder/issues/167

### Slugbuilder [deis/slugbuilder](https://github.com/deis/slugbuilder)
* [x] Every demo app builds correctly
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to monitor component~~

### Slugrunner [deis/slugrunner](https://github.com/deis/slugrunner)
* ~~Metrics: expose operational metrics to monitor component~~

### Logger [deis/logger](https://github.com/deis/logger)
* [x] Logging sub-system internals documented
* [x] Functioning `deis logs` for all apps
* [x] Platform log-draining + documentation
* Availability:
    * Strategy: RC=1
    * Needs health check: deis/logger#19
    * Does not need to survive restart

### Monitoring [deis/monitor](https://github.com/deis/monitor)
* [ ] Monitor sub-system internals documented
* [ ] Default monitors for workflow components: availability/health only

",{},{}
