If conda is really going to a production system, it needs to operate more dependably and consistently. I often run into situations where conda basically gives up and says ""there is a problem and I can't fix it."" But my biggest gripe is that conda can create an entire environment that is broken without even realizing it.

I provide a repeatable example below.

