Microsoft Peering Arguments
    --advertised-public-prefixes: List of prefixes to be advertised through the BGP peering.
                                  Required to set up Microsoft Peering.
    --customer-asn              : Autonomous system number of the customer.
    --routing-registry-name     : Internet Routing Registry / Regional Internet Registry.  Allowed
                                  values: AFRINIC, ALTDB, APNIC, ARIN, LACNIC, LEVEL3, RADB,
                                  RIPENCC.


However it’s available in the “create” operation:

Command
    az network express-route peering create: Create peering settings.

Arguments
    --circuit-name          [Required]: ExpressRoute circuit name.
    --peer-asn              [Required]: Autonomous system number of the customer/connectivity
