6803,IssuesEvent,2015-03-08 20:14:21+00:00,23984796,jupyter/nbgrader,83444,jhamrick,7388996,jupyter,opened,autopep8 is not language agnostic,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jupyter/nbgrader/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"At some point I added in autopep8 to help with computing checksums of grade cells, but this actually shouldn't be there because it's not language agnostic. It would be nice to have something like this, because it should be ok if students accidentally add e.g. a space or a newline to one of the grading cells, but I don't know what the best way is to do this in a language agnostic way.",{},{}
