7040,IssuesEvent,2017-09-19 15:31:34+00:00,98336690,deepmind/pysc2,256625,tewalds,8596759,deepmind,closed,Remote environment with Windows Server 2012.,[],[],3,"I tried to run 
""python -m pysc2.bin.agent --map Simple64""
using Remote Desktop. (local: Windows 10, remote: Windows 2012)

However it failed with the message 
""Running Starcraft II Through a Remote Desktop Connection is Not Supported. Exiting Program.""
which seems like same : http://www.blizzhackers.cc/viewtopic.php?f=220&t=487510

To work around this, it tried to connected remote server using Power Shell with command ""Enter_PSSession""
Executing ""python -m pysc2.bin.agent --map Simple64"" with remote session create Starcraft 2 process, and soon Blizzard_Error process, which seems like the same as the case above.

Is there any method to solve this problem, or work around this?",{},{}
