7699,IssuesEvent,2017-02-09 17:31:21+00:00,33660979,computationalmodelling/nbval,327925,takluyver,11869420,computationalmodelling,closed,Should we allow non-execution of cells for nbval?,"[{'id': 197568170, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/computationalmodelling/nbval/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],2,"We have a keyword `#NBVAL_IGNORE_OUTPUT` (see issue #16) that stops nbval from comparing the computed output against the stored output for the input cell in which the string `#NBVAL_IGNORE_OUTPUT` is found. However, the input cell code is still executed. This is normally useful as later cells may depend on it.

Would it be useful to also support another feature, maybe using the keyword `#NBVAL_IGNORE`, which means that the input cell in which this is found will not be executed at all? This could be used in cases where we know that the execution causes side effects on the host that executes the command, which we may not want or need as part of the nbval testing. ",{},{}
7704,IssuesEvent,2015-12-07 21:58:35+00:00,22783065,project-generator/project_generator,2963726,0xc0170,11992191,project-generator,opened,Tools - provide specific version for tools,[],[],0,"We don't currently version our templates for tools. For instance, iar_arm is using IAR syntax valid for v7.x, thus we should start describe better what our tools provide. 

For iar, it would be iar_arm_v7 for instance (iar_arm would be for the latest one always). uvision has also v4 and v5. In many cases , changes are not backward compatible and not everybody can afford updating their tools. However, we won't support all versions in the long run!",{},{}
