7879,IssuesEvent,2017-12-04 01:12:10+00:00,51397392,pytroll/satpy,1828519,davidh-ssec,13004956,pytroll,opened,Python 2 Cruft,"[{'id': 323805264, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 751601587, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/good%20first%20contribution', 'name': 'good first contribution', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 323805265, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'davidh-ssec', 'id': 1828519, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1828519?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/davidh-ssec', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"This issue describes the various code pieces that should be removed or modified when Python 2 support is eventually removed from SatPy in order to keep the code clean. It will likely be difficult to keep this issue up to date, but I figure it would be good to make an attempt. SatPy maintainers should update the bulleted list below. SatPy contributors (no issue editing permissions) should comment with code lines/blocks that need to modified and how.

 - [ ] `yaml_reader.py`: Use of abstractproperty is deprecated in Python 3.3+. It should be replaced by `@property` followed by `@abstractmethod`: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html#abc.abstractmethod

These changes don't all have to occur in one PR. They *can't* be merged until SatPy's Python 2.7 support is dropped which is will likely be some time shortly after numpy's support of it is dropped.",{},{}
7889,IssuesEvent,2016-01-07 11:44:00+00:00,1962269,django-webtest/django-webtest,355454,Flimm,13016086,django-webtest,opened,Document use with SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT enabled,[],[],0,"I have `SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT` enabled, and it's causing some issues for me.

    class CommentsTest(WebTest):
        def test_thingy(self):
            response = self.app.get(""/page1"")
            self.assertEquals(response.status_code, 200)

This fails, because the status is 302, a redirect from http:// to https://

So I tried using the `extra_environ` keyword argument:

            extra_environ = {'wsgi.url_scheme': 'https', 'SERVER_PORT': '443'}
            response = self.app.get(""/page1"", extra_environ=extra_environ}
            self.assertEquals(response.status_code, 200)

This works, but then the subsequent code doesn't:

            form = response.forms['comment-form']
            form.submit(extra_environ=extra_environ)

This actually submits to `https://localhost:80/comment/post`. Notice the port 80 even though it is over HTTPS.

I tried adding this decorator:

        @override_settings(SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=False)
        def test_thingy(self):
            # ...

But then I got 403 forbidden errors, because of missing CSRF tokens. This doesn't happen on my development machine (where `SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT` is disabled).

I'm not sure what to do now, and it seems to me that django-webtest should set up HTTPS better in the case where `SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT` is set to true, or at least document the workaround.",{},{}
