8462,IssuesEvent,2017-02-16 01:00:13+00:00,51442999,python-cmd2/cmd2,2812720,tleonhardt,17161025,python-cmd2,closed,List all help as one-liners,"[{'id': 324131052, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 324180750, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/minor', 'name': 'minor', 'color': 'bfe5bf', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Originally reported by: **Anonymous**

---

I find it efficient to list a summary of help for all documented commands. Thought you might find this worth including. Thanks for a nice tool! --Ken Bannister

```
#!python
    self.doc_header = 'Commands (type ""help all"" or ""help <topic>""):'

    def help_all(self):
        """"""Lists first line of help for all documented commands""""""
        names = self.get_names()
        names.sort()
        for name in names:
            if name[:3] == 'do_':
                try:
                    doc = getattr(self, name).__doc__
                    if doc:
                        maxlen = 65
                        ellipsis = ''
                        if len(doc) > maxlen:
                            ellipsis = '...'
                        self.stdout.write('{0} - {1}{2}\n'.format(
                                    name[3:80-maxlen], doc[:maxlen], ellipsis))
                except AttributeError:
                    pass
```

---
- Bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/catherinedevlin/cmd2/issue/5
",{},{}
