<pre>
<b>What steps will reproduce the problem?</b>

import rdflib
rdflib.graph.Graph().parse(source=""http://w3c.org/doesnotexist"")

<b>What is the expected output? What do you see instead?</b>

HTTPError

<b>What version of the product are you using? On what operating system?</b>

Exception('""%s"" while trying to open ""%s""' % (e, self.url))

Instead of raising its own Exception why not take the Exception we get from urlopen()?

line 92:
-        try:
-            file = urlopen(req)
-        except HTTPError, e:
-            # TODO:
-            raise Exception('""%s"" while trying to open ""%s""' % (e, self.url))
+
+        file = urlopen(req)
+

